  "title": "priceRangeConnector doesn't display values",
  "body": "We're using the jQuery-connector for priceRanges, to gain more control over the look and feel of the element. \r\n\r\nWhen using the example given @ https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/dev/app/jquery/widgets/priceRanges.js, all is well (RefinedValues are shown and resultset changes) except for the fact that the input boxes aren't updated with the value entered.\r\n\r\nOne would expect that the entered value remains visible.\r\n\r\n![schermafbeelding 2018-12-12 om 11 03 32](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16369103/49862218-f98b2880-fdfd-11e8-9bbf-aed2f80c3c11.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nkind regards, Marco\r\n\r\np.s. The demo @ https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=jquery&selectedStory=PriceRanges.default doesn't work either ...\r\n",
